@Puzzled Brit 

As you may already know or have figured out, in American English, the word "school" is applicable to universities and colleges as well as primary or elementary schools, middle schools and high schools.

Colleges are also different, as they are basically the same as universities, although the difference, if any, is one of size and the number of programs offered, especially graduate programs.  Within a university, there are often divisions also called colleges, but when a student of such a university is asked what college he or she attends, the normal answer is the name of the university.

